<center><font size=7><b>Ghosts 'n' Goblins</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 5</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>On level 3, in order to see the Princess you must go right until you meet a
ladder.  Having reached it, go up it and forge to the right again, until
you find a way down.  Go down, and then go right along a tunnel until you
encounter three den beasts.  Be warned, there are a lot of zombies and a
few gremlins as well.  When you come to the Princess you will have to
defeat two large gremlins.  Ah, true love!" Thanks Andy...<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oh.  What happened to the dragon mentioned in your preview on Ghosts 'n'
Goblins?  Is he there or is he just invisible?
 <i>(Andy Bowden in Your Sinclair issue 10)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Game bugs</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>When you get to the monster's warehouse, keep on going up the ladders until
you get to the top.  Lose your suit.  If you then jump while a bird is
coming towards you you get killed.  Your bones should hit the top of the
warehouse and the game will stop and crash.
 <i>(Paul in Your Sinclair issue 10)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALLIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Infinite Lives</td><td>36057,182</td></tr>
<tr><td>Lives = x</td><td>25177,x:49047,x&nbsp;(x= 1-255)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infinite Time</td><td>38303,0</td></tr>
</table>
<BR><BR><B>Change x to whatever value you wish, using the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Type-in hacks</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/SinclairUser/Issue95/Tape/">this issue of Poke City</a>.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Sinclair User issue 95)</i> 

<br><hr>
This hack'll give you infinite lives<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<pre>
10 CLEAR 65000
20 LOAD ""CODE
30 POKE 65277,200: POKE 65281,245: POKE 65256,111: POKE 65257,85
40 FOR N=65477 TO 65496: READ A: POKE N,A: NEXT N
50 RANDOMIZE USR 65224
60 DATA 33,208,255,34,174,96,1,112,234,197,201,33,191,194,34,217,140,195,3,128
</pre>
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
